# CI and releases

## CI (every push/PR to `main`)

- Workflow: `.github/workflows/ci.yml` → calls `reusable-tests.yml` (Linux, macOS, Windows).
- Badge in README tracks `ci.yml` on `main` (~3–5 min; badge cache can lag).
- Manual run: **Actions → CI → Run workflow** (branch `main`), or `gh workflow run ci.yml --repo MrChriZ/StuckInTheMD --ref main`.
- If pushes stop triggering runs or jobs stay **queued** with 0 jobs: see [.github/ACTIONS_TROUBLESHOOTING.md](.github/ACTIONS_TROUBLESHOOTING.md) and [githubstatus.com](https://www.githubstatus.com) (Actions degraded).

## Release notes (required before every release)

- **Source of truth:** `RELEASE_NOTES.md` at repo root — one `## vX.Y.Z` section per version with bullet points.
- **Generated artifact:** `dist/release-notes-vX.Y.Z.md` (created by the installer build; do not commit `dist/`).
- **Scripts:**
  - `.\scripts\generate-release-notes.ps1` — extract notes for current or `-Version` from `CMakeLists.txt`
  - `bash scripts/generate-release-notes.sh [version]` — same on POSIX
- **When bumping version:** edit `RELEASE_NOTES.md` first, then bump `project(StuckInTheMD VERSION …)` in `CMakeLists.txt`.

## Release checklist

1. Add or update the `## vX.Y.Z` section in `RELEASE_NOTES.md`.
2. `.\scripts\run-tests.ps1` or `bash scripts/run-tests.sh`
3. Push to `main` — wait for **CI** green
4. Bump `CMakeLists.txt` version, commit, push
5. Build locally (validates notes + installer):
   ```powershell
   .\scripts\publish-windows-release.ps1
   ```
   Or step-by-step: `run-tests.ps1` → `build-windows-installer.ps1`
6. `git tag vX.Y.Z && git push origin vX.Y.Z` — Release workflow uploads installer + `body_path` from generated notes
7. If Actions did not run, publish manually:
   ```powershell
   .\scripts\publish-windows-release.ps1 -Publish
   ```

## Release workflow (on `v*` tags)

- `.github/workflows/release.yml` runs **full test matrix first** (`needs: tests`), then builds the Windows installer (which generates release notes), then creates the GitHub Release using `dist/release-notes-vX.Y.Z.md`.
- Failed tests **block** upload — do not tag until CI is green.

## Windows installer (local)

```powershell
cmake --build build --config Release --target stuckinthemd
.\scripts\build-windows-installer.ps1 -SkipBuild   # also writes dist/release-notes-v*.md
```

Output: `dist/StuckInTheMD-<version>-setup.exe` (requires Inno Setup 6).

Do not force-push tags or amend pushed release commits unless the user asks.
